<doc id="774080" wikidata="Q479094" url="?curid=774080" title="Calvörde (Amt)">
<text>The Amt of Calvörde is a historical Amt in the District of Helmstedt, Brunswick, in today&#x27;s Saxony-Anhalt, Germany. It formed an exclave that was surrounded by the Province of Saxony, Prussia, and in 1944 it was moved to the District of Haldensleben, Province of Saxony. Its capital was Calvörde; it had a population of 4,600 (1933).

Municipalities in 1939:
* Berenbrock
* Calvörde
* Dorst
* Elsebeck
* Jeseritz
* Lössewitz
* Parleib
* Uthmöden
* Velsdorf
* Zobbenitz
